  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Using a rapidly responding nitric oxide analyzer in a new developed modular
      lung-function-setup we are going to measure steady-state NO diffusing capacity in 107 healthy
      subjects (age 6-45 years). The results will be compared to those measured by using carbon
      monoxide single-breath estimates. We like to show that the new method is sufficient to
      measure exactly lung diffusion capacity in this collective.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
